时空定律的笔记
Notes on the Law of Time and Space

我以价格为坐标，  
记录能量的流向。  
每一次波动，  
都是一场力与质量的实验。  
I take price as the axis,  
and record the flow of energy.  
Each fluctuation  
is an experiment in force and mass.

牛顿的定律依然成立，  
但我在其中加入了波形，  
让“力”不再只是推与抗，  
而成了意图在时间里的投影。  
Newton’s laws still hold,  
yet I add waveforms to their geometry.  
Force is no longer mere push and resistance,  
but the projection of intent through time.

在周期的计算中，  
开普勒的第三定律重新出现。  
行星与资产——皆为运行体，  
轨道之外，并无例外。  
In the computation of cycles,  
Kepler’s third law reemerges.  
Planets and assets alike are bodies in motion;  
there are no exceptions beyond the orbit.

爱因斯坦的能量方程  
提供了最宏观的平衡：  
当价格被压缩到极限，  
潜能以光速释放。  
Einstein’s energy equation  
offers the grand symmetry of balance:  
when price compresses to its limit,  
potential releases at the velocity of light.

声学为我提供了图像——  
频率，是人类行为的和声。  
低频为趋势，高频为噪音，  
而真理总在共振之点显现。  
Acoustics lend me their imagery—  
frequency as the harmony of human behavior.  
Low frequency reveals trend, high frequency noise,  
and truth appears only where resonance aligns.

我测量脉冲，取样恒星。  
太阳的直径、月球的周期，  
乃至地球心跳的微振，  
都在市场数据中重演。  
I measure pulses and sample starlight.  
The Sun’s diameter, the Moon’s orbit,  
even the Earth’s faint heartbeat—  
all return in the data of the markets.

这一切并非偶然。  
自然的秩序延伸到人类的交易；  
数学的意志在金属与货币间回响；  
时间与价格，只是同一力量的两种单位。  
None of this is coincidence.  
Nature’s order extends into human trade;  
the will of mathematics echoes in metal and currency;  
time and price are twin units of the same force.

于是我写下定律：  
F = ma，可映射为价格的加速度；  
E = mc²，对应市场的潜在能量；  
T³ = r²，揭示波动的周期秩序。  
Thus I record the laws:  
F = ma, mapped to the acceleration of price;  
E = mc², equal to potential volatility;  
T³ = r², describing the periodic order of movement.

在这些公式的交点上，  
我找到了一种统一：  
科学与金融并非分裂之学，  
它们都在寻求——  
宇宙运转的终极方程。  
At the intersection of these equations,  
I find a form of unity:  
science and finance are not divided disciplines—  
both seek the final equation  
of the universe in motion.

